備註 Remarks





基本素養 Basic Literacy
□ 人文素養
 Humanities.
■ 誠信與務實素養
 Honesty and pragmatic.
□ 善待環境之胸懷
 Environment-caring manners.
□ 國際視野
 International perspective.
 

核心能力 Competence
■ 環工領域之專業知識，規劃與設計系統之能力
 Professional knowledge in environmental engineering, and ability for planning and designing system.
■ 策劃及執行環保專題研究和撰寫論文之能力
 Planning and execute environmental protection case study and writing papers.
■ 運用科學及工程知識的能力
 The ability to use science and engineering knowledge.
■ 創新思考及獨立解決問題之能力
 Creative thinking and independent problem-solving ability.
□ 領導管理及與不同領域人員協調整合之能力
 Leadership management and negotiation with other fields’ experts.
■ 國際觀和良好外語能力
 Global vision and excellent foreign languages ability.
□ 專業倫理、瞭解社會責任與能終身學習的能力
 Professional ethics, society responsibility understanding, and lifelong learning ability.
 

課程概述 Course Description
       Course name：Chemical Principle for Environmental Engineering
Course code	P560200	Credits	3	Lecturer	Yeh, Hsuan-Hsien；Cheng, Sheng-Shung
Course Description：
The course begins with a review of the basic chemical thermodynamics and kinetics. The main contents include: introduction to acids and bases, equilibriums calculations with both algebraic and graphical techniques, titration and buffer intensity. Aqueous carbonate (with open and closed to atmosphere) systems. Alkalinity and acidity. Then, the interaction between atmosphere and water, precipitation and dissolution, oxidation and reduction and its kinetics.
Finally, solid-water interface and particle-particle interaction, including electric double layer theory, colloid stability, DLVO theory, and electrokinetic phenomena.
Objectives：
Textbooks :
Stumm, W. and Morgan, J.J. Aquatic Chemistry, 3rd ed., John Wiley & Sons, 1996.
Reference books：
Jensen, J.N. A Problem-Solving Approach to Aquatic Chemistry, John Wiley & Sons, 2003.
Snoeyink, V.L. and Jenkins, D. Water Chemistry, John Wiley & Sons, 1980.
Benjamin, M.M. Water Chemistry, McGraw-Hill, 2002.
Pankow, J.F. Aquatic Chemistry Concepts, Lewis Publishers, 1991.
Evangelou, V.P. Environmental Soil and Water Chemistry, John Wiley & Sons, 1998.
vanLoon, G.W. and Duffy, S.J. Environmental Chemistry: A Global Perspective, Oxford University Press, 2000.
Webpage：
